frameDefinitions: This frame concerns transparent nouns that denote Instances of Types of entities or events.
This frame has to do with nouns denoting types of entities.
An Entity meets the pre-conditions for participating in an Event.
The Agent immobilizes a Patient optionally,  to an Anchor.
There exist a number of different possible Situations that may happen in the future.
An Entity is in a specified State.
frameExamples: The survey confirmed that management interference in team operations had increased , and <t><fex name='Instance'>instances</fex></t> of management decisions being taken without team consultation had also increased .
I don't like this newfangled <t><fex name='Subtype'>kind</fex></t> of  fish.
Conductor software gives us the hands-on <t>capability</t> to provide updates immediately
The junior officer <t>handcuffed</t> his commanding officer to his desk.
You have but two <t><fex name='Situation'>choices</fex></t> for your daughter .
Some of the classics were in excellent <t>condition</t>.
listRoleDefinitions: A thing or episode of a certain <fen>Type</fen>.
The category of thing or event of which an <fen>Instance</fen> is picked out.
The entity which denotes a subtype of the more general <fen>Category</fen>.
The more general type that the target denotes a subtype of. This role is obligatory and should be labeled DNI when not present.
The <fen>Entity</fen> whose meeting or falling short of pre-conditions is assessed.
The <fen>Event</fen> that the <fen>Entity</fen> may participate in.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> is capable of the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is immobilized by the <fen>Agent</fen>, optionally to an <fen>Anchor</fen>.
Something that may happen in the future, or at least whose factual status is unresolved. This is often tagged in a second role layer and generally contains the target.

An individual involved in the <fen>Event</fen>.

'<fex name='Agent'>You</fex> have a <t>choice</t>.'
An entity intimately involved in the <fen>Event</fen>.
The entity whose <fen>State</fen> is specified and/or evaluated.
A relation in which the <fen>Entity</fen> participates or a property that the <fen>Entity</fen> possesses.
